article.headline: South Alabama 71, Denver 33
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- Demetric Bennett scored a game-high 24 points to lead South Alabama to a 71-33 victory over Denver on Sunday. Daon Merritt added 12 and Domonic Tilford scored 10 for South Alabama (17-3, 9-0 Sun Belt Conference). Nate Rohner had 10 for Denver (8-11, 4-4). He was the team's only player in double figures. South Alabama had a 41-14 lead at halftime and outscored Denver 30-22 in the paint.
